Since 2005, human rights advocates have returned to the Ford Bridge in Moore to reenact the lynching of two black couples (Roger and Dorothy Malcom and George Mae and Murray Dorsey) by the Ku Klux Klan in 1946.
So far, no one's been charged with the murders.
Tyrone Brooks, who helped organize the revival, said: "It's inconceivable that we see them in our communities, that we know who they are, but not one person has been arrested in all these years".
