I fell in love with her and made an offer that day".
After the initial meeting, the 1,000-square-foot apartment was renovated from the ground up.
Originally a one-room property with a complicated plan, you had to go through the kitchen to get to the bedroom, and Joanne wanted to add a storage area and a hanging floor to take full advantage of the generous ceiling height.
"High ceilings, big windows and lots of wanted light.
This is my run".
To this end, Notting Hill-based architecture and design studio Duck & Shed hired Erfan Azadi to take advantage of the 12.5 ft ceiling and create not only a structure but also a place for Joanne to live.
