But the dinosaur's undersea tomb preserved its armor in exquisite detail.
The fossilised remains of this particular species are so well preserved that bits of skin still cover the convex armor layers along the dinosaur's skull.
As Michael Greshko wrote for National Geographic, a conservation of this degree is "as rare as winning the lottery.
The more I look at it, the more incredible it is.
